    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2-3: IgSF21 is a postsynaptic protein that interacts specifically with neurexin2α (gene NRXN2) and not any of the other neurexin isoforms.\n\nFigure 7: IgSF21 knockout reduces (but does not abolish) synaptic transmission.\n\nAuthors propose that IgSF21 modulates synaptic transmission through trans-synaptic signaling via neurexin2α.. Experimental description: Result section, Figure 7 legend: \"Inhibitory synaptic transmission is reduced in Igsf21 -/- mice\"\n\nM&M: \" Igsf21 -/- mice were bred into the C57BL/6 background. Genotyping of Igsf21 -/-mice was performed using the following two primers: P1 (5'-TCA GAC AAT GGT CCC TAT GAG-3') and P2 (5'-CTC ATG GCA CTT GCT CCT TG-3').\"",
